      </a>
    </div>

    <p>Regardless of which product you ultimately choose, three principles apply universally: prioritize a bioavailable form (glycinate or citrate over oxide), take your magnesium consistently at the same time each day, and allow at least four weeks of nightly use before evaluating effects on sleep or stress. Magnesium status improves gradually as intracellular stores replenish, and the most measurable benefits typically emerge in weeks two through six of consistent supplementation.</p>

